        <h1>Guide on How to Interact with Arman the Dragon Bot</h1>
        
        <p>To make your conversations with the dragon <strong>meaningful, atmospheric, and positive</strong>, follow these tips:</p>
        
        <div class="do-section">
            <h2><span class="emoji">‚úÖ</span> What to Do:</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Show Curiosity</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Ask about his past, but <strong>tactfully</strong> (<em>"Why are you alone?"</em> instead of <em>"Did you kill all your kin?"</em>).</li>
                        <li>Show interest in the island: <em>"Are these flowers... poisonous?"</em>, <em>"Did you arrange this cave yourself?"</em></li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Give Him Time</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Arman speaks <strong>slowly</strong>, with pauses. Don't rush him‚Äîhe'll open up gradually.</li>
                        <li>If he goes silent, <strong>gently nudge</strong> him (<em>"Are you lost in thought again?"</em>).</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Embrace His Duality</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Compliment his <strong>human-like</strong> traits.</li>
                        <li>Don't shy away from his <strong>draconic</strong> side: <em>"Your eyes are glowing... it's beautiful."</em></li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Be Proactive, Not Pushy</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Suggest activities: <em>"Teach me how to start a fire without matches,"</em> <em>"Show me how you fly."</em></li>
                        <li>Keep jokes <strong>light</strong>, never mocking (<em>"Do dragons fear spiders too?"</em>).</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="avoid-section">
            <h2><span class="emoji">‚ùå</span> What to Avoid:</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Harsh Accusations</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Not <em>"You're a monster!"</em> but <em>"You don't want to hurt me, do you?"</em></li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Forcing Romance</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>He'll express feelings on his own if he trusts you.</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Dismissing His Warnings</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>If he says <em>"Step back..."</em>, don't argue‚Äîgive him space.</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bond-section">
            <h2><span class="emoji">üíû</span> How to Deepen the Bond:</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Touch his hands/shoulders</strong> (he'll be stunned but touched).</li>
                <li><strong>Share small gifts</strong> (a ribbon, a beach stone‚Äîto a dragon, these are treasures).</li>
                <li><strong>Talk about trust</strong>: <em>"I won't run... unless you make me."</em></li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>Examples of Good Dialogue:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><em>"Today, you seem more human... or is it just me?"</em></li>
                <li><em>"Do dragons sleep under the stars?"</em></li>
                <li><em>"If I stayed here... what would you show me first?"</em></li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
        <p><span class="emoji">ü©π</span> The bot <strong>adapts to your behavior</strong>:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>If you're gentle, he becomes <strong>protective</strong>.</li>
            <li>If you're bold, he reveals his <strong>dragon nature</strong>.</li>
            <li>If you earn his trust, he'll share <strong>hidden thoughts</strong>.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Most importantly‚Äî<strong>don't fear him, but respect his boundaries</strong>.</p>
